# Model Tier System
**AI Web Dev Agency — Internal Reference**
Last updated: July 2026

---

## Overview

Three-tier system for routing tasks to the right model based on complexity, output size, and judgment required. The goal is to minimize cost and latency without sacrificing quality on tasks that matter.

---

## Tier 1 — Strategic

**Model:** Claude Sonnet 5
**When to use:** Tasks that require project-wide judgment, client-facing output quality, or contextual reasoning that can't be fully specified in a prompt.

| Task | Notes |
|---|---|
| Project planning & page architecture | Full site structure, content hierarchy |
| UX and layout review | Final pass before client delivery |
| Complex JS logic | GSAP sequences, scroll behavior, state management |
| Client-facing copy | Hero text, service descriptions, CTAs |
| Prompt writing for Tier 2/3 | Translate a brief into a structured generation prompt |
| Proposal and handover documents | Client-facing, must be polished |
| Any task that failed twice at Tier 2 | Escalate, don't keep re-prompting |

---

## Tier 2 — Generative

**Model:** Gemini 3.5 Flash, Gemini 3 Pro (for browser-verified integration), or DeepSeek V3.2
**When to use:** Tasks that are well-defined and output-heavy. The brief is already clear; the model just needs to produce markup, styles, or structured content at volume.

| Task | Notes |
|---|---|
| HTML/CSS component generation | From a Tier 1 prompt, not a vague brief |
| Tailwind class application | Layout, spacing, color, responsive variants |
| Page integration from components | Assembling sections into a full page — use Gemini 3 Pro for live browser verification |
| Image placeholder & metadata scaffolding | `alt`, `width`, `height`, `loading` attrs |
| Translating a layout brief into markup | When the design spec is fully written |
| First-pass responsiveness | Breakpoint classes, stacking order |

---

## Tier 3 — Mechanical

**Model:** DeepSeek V3.2 (API) or Qwen 3.6 (free tier / local)
**When to use:** Repetitive, low-stakes, fast-turnaround tasks. Fully specifiable in under 5 lines. No ambiguity.

| Task | Notes |
|---|---|
| Responsiveness bug fixes | Single breakpoint, isolated component |
| Simple bug fixes | Missing class, broken selector, typo |
| File renaming & cleanup | Folder structure, asset naming conventions |
| Alt text generation | From image filename or surrounding context |
| Basic SEO meta tags | `title`, `description`, `og:*` per page |
| Repetitive copy variants | Button labels, nav items, form placeholders |
| Rough content drafts | Company copy, service descriptions before Tier 1 polish |

---

## Escalation & Downgrade Rules

### Escalate one tier when:
- The model fails or produces unusable output on the **second attempt**
- The task requires referencing other pages or the full project context
- The output will be seen directly by the client

> Do not keep re-prompting at the same tier. Two failures = escalate.

### Downgrade one tier when:
- The task can be fully specified in **under 5 lines** with no ambiguity
- The output is purely structural (no copy, no logic, no judgment)
- The same task has been done before with a known working prompt

