## Cost & Speed Reference

| Tier | Model | Relative Cost | Best For |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Claude Sonnet 5 | $$$ | Quality, judgment, client output |
| 2 | Gemini 3.5 Flash | $ | Volume generation, fast turnaround |
| 2 | Gemini 3 Pro | $$ | Integration with live browser verification |
| 2/3 | DeepSeek V3.2 | $ | Cheap general-purpose, HTML/CSS and drafting |
| 3 | Qwen 3.6 (free/local) | Free | Content drafts, mechanical tasks, zero API cost |

---

## Decision Flowchart

```
Is the task client-facing or does it require full project context?
  → YES → Tier 1 (Claude Sonnet 5)

Is the task fully defined with no ambiguity?
  → NO  → Write a Tier 1 prompt first, then re-route
  → YES → Continue

Can it be specified in under 5 lines with a known output format?
  → YES → Tier 3 (DeepSeek V3.2 / Qwen 3.6)
  → NO  → Tier 2 (Gemini 3.5 Flash / 3 Pro)
```

---

## Notes

- DeepSeek V3.2 handles low-to-mid HTML/CSS generation and content drafting well, and is significantly cheaper than Claude for volume work.
- Qwen 3.6 (free tier or local via Ollama) is best for tasks where privacy matters (client data in context), offline work, or zero-budget drafting.
- This system applies per-task, not per-project. A single page build might hit all three tiers.
- Revisit model assignments every few months — the landscape moves fast.
